Introduction

DKZ (formerly known as Dongkiz) is a South Korean boy group formed by Dongyo Entertainment. The group was originally 8 but now consists of five members.

DKZ debuted under their original name Dongkiz with a pre-debut single released on November 21, 2018, and officially entered the kpop scene on April 24, 2019, with their first single album "DONGKIZ On The Block." The initial lineup included members Wondae and Munik, who later went on hiatus in August 2021 due to health concerns, leaving the group to promote temporarily as a trio.

A major rebranding took place on March 18, 2022, when the group was renamed to DKZ. The relaunch coincided with the release of "Chase Episode 2. Maum" and marked a new chapter with the addition of three new members: Sehyeon, Giseok, and Mingyu. It was also announced that Wondae had officially withdrawn from the group.

Munik’s departure was confirmed in February 2023 after an extended hiatus. Later that year, on August 7, 2023, member Kyoungyoon also left the group following a controversy related to his family, further solidifying the current five-member formation.
